OL,4,CElisa Loncon: From poverty to PhD to
OL,5,Cwriting Chile's constitution
OL,6, In the 1970s, as Elisa Loncon was
OL,7, growing up, she had to travel 8km (five
OL,8, miles) to reach school. Her family,
OL,9, from Chile's Mapuche indigenous
OL,10, community, lived in poverty in a remote
OL,11, village in the southern Araucania
OL,12, region. There was no-one to take her to
OL,13, classes, and very often, the only way
OL,14, to make the journey was on foot through
OL,15, dirt roads.
OL,18,FBut she did not give up.
